companyProfile.companyDescription: Avenue Supermarts Limited is an India-based company, which is engaged in the business of organized retail and operating supermarkets under the DMart brand name. DMart is a supermarket chain that offers customers a range of products with a focus on the foods, non-foods fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) and general merchandise and apparel product categories. Its stores stock home utility products, including food, toiletries, beauty products, garments, kitchenware, bed and bath linen, home appliances and others. The Company offers its products under various categories, such as bed and bath, dairy and frozen, fruits and vegetables, crockery, toys and games, kids’ apparel, ladies’ garments, apparel for men, home and personal care, daily essentials, grocery, and staples. DMart operates approximately 365 stores and has a presence across Maharashtra, Gujarat, Andhra Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Karnataka, Telangana, and Chhattisgarh.

recentNews.headline: DMart share price cracks 6% amid reports of  ?634-crore block deal in Radhakishan Damani-led stock
recentNews.intro: Radhakishan Damani-led Avenue Supermarts share price has gained 3% in one month and 14% in three months. The DMart share price has rallied 15% in 2025 so far, while the stock has fallen 14% in one year.
recentNews.imagecaption: DMart shares have risen 13% over the past two years, while the stock has delivered 72% returns in five years.

recentNews.headline: Axis Securities raises Nifty target to 26,300 for March 2026; top stock picks include HDFC Bank, SBI, and others
recentNews.intro: Axis Securities has raised its Nifty 50 target to 26,300 for March 2026, citing strong earnings and market sentiment. While a near-term consolidation is anticipated due to global uncertainties, the firm remains bullish on domestic sectors and has adjusted its portfolio to focus on quality stocks.

recentNews.headline: Q4 earnings watch: Consumption giants drive revenue but lag in profits
recentNews.intro: In the latest edition of Q4FY25 earnings series, Mint explores the financial health of the consumption-focused market leaders compared to the rest of India Inc.
recentNews.imagecaption: Data shows that 13 consumption-driven companies from the Nifty India Consumption Index, which includes firms deriving over half their revenue from domestic demand, saw their aggregate revenue grow 11.9% year-on-year. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: Quick commerce is coming for DMart?s turf
recentNews.intro: DMart?s margins are under pressure as quick commerce players expand aggressively into urban grocery and essentials. With general merchandise sales still weak and operating costs rising, Avenue Supermarts faces its stiffest competition yet.
recentNews.imagecaption: In Q4FY25, Avenue?s standalone Ebitda margin fell to 6.8%, the lowest in the past ten quarters at least. (File Photo)

recentNews.headline: DMart shares decline 3% post Q4 Results; More than 6000 crore wealth erosion for Radhakishan Damani & other promoters
recentNews.intro: Stock Market Today: DMart share price declined 3% in the morning trades on Monday post Q4 Results that were declared by Avenue Supermarts over the weekend. The ace investor Radhakishan Damani and other promoters holding 74.65%  stake in the company see notional wealth erosion of more than 6000 crore
recentNews.imagecaption: Stock Market Today: DMart share price declines post Q4 Results;
